Germany Can Close Reactors Without Paying, FT Deutschland Says

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-05-13T05:40:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/germany-can-close-reactors-without-paying-ft-deutschland-says.html
Germany  can shut down older nuclear
power plants without compensating the operators for losses,
 Financial Times Deutschland  said, citing comments by Emil
Schmalfuss, the minister of justice in the state of Schleswig-
Holstein. 